				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Zek<a name="12141"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 13 03 10:21 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Zek is not over cap or stacking haste.  It is spell haste.
<br />

<br />
Erjav can stack with item AND spell haste, to get another 10% pure haste into the mix.  But it is rarely sung by Bards over 60, since Item and spell/song haste caps folks out already. 
<br />

<br />
The best item haste is 41 (45% drop in POT),  and the best spell/song haste is 70, add em up, you are over 100, meaning MOST over 60 folks hit the cap easily, since most melee at 63 have a 40% or better haste item.  Zek gets them to the 100% cap IF the bard is the primary haster.  But most groups and all raids at this level will have shaman or chanter haste though, so why is this song still in the twist? 
<br />

<br />
The DS and ATK buffs.  ATK is a hard stat to buff, not many buffs or items out there affect attack.  Yeah I know there are Vengeance items and Ranger buffs for Atk, but raw ATK buffs arent that common.
<br />

<br />
Rizlonas puts folks at 30% over cap.  There cannot be that many items out there that both stack with the riz effect AND are over cap haste, so I doubt very many folks are concerned with the 160% hard cap anyway.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
